8fPHN2A02 is in fact just a tree editor, the structure of the trees one manipulates 
being defined by the user.  Its strength lies in the flexibility with which one can 
define the logical structure of formulae and how they are to be laid out on the 
screen, and in the ease with which one can select, copy and rearrange 
subexpressions in a mathematical formula.

In summary,  8fPHN2A02 has been designed as a hybrid between WYSIWYG
and macro-based document preparation systems.   It will appeal to you if your
work demands the  comprehensiveness, power and flexibility of a logical-design
system like 8fPHN2A0P or 8fPHN2A0Q.   If you choose to use 8fPHN2A02 you will not be 
sacrificing any of these advantages.  (Nor will you have to rewrite your old 
documents: a 8fPHN2A02 document can include any amount of raw 8fPHN2A0P or 
8fPHN2A0Q code.   No special conversion program is necessary.)  On the other hand, 
you will gain the indispensable advantage of a visual design system so that you
can read what you have written as you write.   

8fPHN2A02 will not fulfil all your dreams.  It was developed as a research 
project in the design of computer interfaces for the writing of mathematical 
documents.  As such its capabilities for editing and viewing 8fPIN2A0@8bOMN0E1plain text are  not so
comprehensive as  conventional editing systems.    Even for the input of
mathematics its ergonomics is hampered by the inhuman nature of
keyboard-mouse  input.   8fPHN2A02 is nevertheless intended as a practical,
pleasant-to-use  system, as judged within the context of current technology,
and one that will  have a place in the emerging generation of computer
interfaces.   

